# BOV Generator API — Railway Environment Variables
# Set all of these in Railway → Project → Variables

# ── API Authentication ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate a strong random key: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
BOV_API_KEY=your-secret-api-key-here

# ── Delivery ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# File delivery is handled in-response: the completed .xlsx is returned as a
# base64-encoded payload in the POST /generate-bov JSON body.  No external
# storage or Microsoft app registration required.
#
# Microsoft Graph / SharePoint delivery (BLOCKED — Northmarq policy prohibits
# Entra app registrations).  Variables listed here for reference only; do not
# set them — they are no longer read by the service:
#
#   AZURE_TENANT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
#   AZURE_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
#   AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here
#   SHAREPOINT_DRIVE_ID=b!xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#   BOV_OUTPUT_FOLDER=BOV Output
